____________________________________________________________________________

                              SERRALINE
____________________________________________________________________________

 COMPILATION
____________________________________________________________________________

 To compile SerraLINE type: make SerraLINE

 If you wish, you can set up flags and the compiler by modifying the Makefile.

____________________________________________________________________________

 USAGE
____________________________________________________________________________

 To run SerraLINE, you must modify the input file "s_line.in", writing the
 locations of the topology and trajectory files. These files must be output
 of WrLINE.

 Once s_line.in is ready, to run SerraLINE type: ./SerraLINE < s_line.in

 This will generate an output file "bending_parameters.out", containing the
 averages and standard deviations at all possible lengths.
 
